nand: omap2: disable NAND sequential cached (continuous) read

On AM335x the continuous-read path (NAND cmd 0x31 streaming), enabled in
6.x when the chip advertises supports_read_cache, is incompatible with the
GPMC prefetch engine. During UBI mount, reading a full LEB via the
continuous-read helper aborts mid-transfer with -110 (ETIMEDOUT); the
underlying flash is fine (direct dd of the same PEB reads cleanly).

Kernel 5.10 has no continuous-read feature and never exhibited this.

Clear chip->parameters.supports_read_cache in omap_nand_attach_chip (which
runs before nand_scan_tail's rawnand_check_cont_read_support), so
supported_op.cont_read is never set. This is the legal way to disable it;
writing supported_op directly would trip WARN_ON_ONCE.

Depends-on: 0001-nand-omap2-elm-eprobe-defer.patch (same file, apply first)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/omap2.c b/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/omap2.c
--- a/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/omap2.c
+++ b/drivers/mtd/nand/raw/omap2.c
@@ -1847,6 +1847,15 @@
 	dma_cap_mask_t mask;
 	int err;
 
+	/* Disable NAND sequential cached (continuous) read. On AM335x the
+	 * cont-read 0x31 streaming path is incompatible with the GPMC prefetch
+	 * engine and causes sporadic -110 mid-LEB during UBI mount. Cleared here
+	 * (attach_chip runs before nand_scan_tail rawnand_check_cont_read_support)
+	 * so supported_op.cont_read is never set - legal, no WARN_ON_ONCE.
+	 * 5.10 had no continuous read; this restores that behaviour.
+	 */
+	chip->parameters.supports_read_cache = false;
+
 	if (chip->bbt_options & NAND_BBT_USE_FLASH)
 		chip->bbt_options |= NAND_BBT_NO_OOB;
 	else
